dfl@panix.com (Danny O'Bedlam) writes:
>In <20r429$r7a@uniwa.uwa.edu.au> markd@uniwa.uwa.edu.au (Mark Diamond) writes:
>
>>I've been following the US Clipper debate with interest, but haven't
>>come across a satement of where Clipper is documented or its intented purpose
>>defined.  Is there such a document?
>
>	Er, Mark?  Clipper was announced to us as a "Classified" algorithm
>already on a chip, courtesy of the good folks at the NSA and Mykotronx of
>Torrence California.

Skipjack is the classified algorithm.

>But the purpose?  It is to give law enforcement much wiretap capacity,
>while you encrypt to your hearts content, the FBI or friendly law
>enforcement agency will be decrypting.

LE already has wiretap capacity. Always has. So does anyone that has a few
bucks and can find a Radio Shack store. The purpose of Clipper is to
eliminate 99% of the eavesdroppers, while allowing LE to have the same
freedom to wiretap as they do today.
